cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with regression trees and forests applied to object pose estimation, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel node splitting method that improves the efficiency of the tree structures, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also applies the proposed method to head pose estimation and car direction estimation, which are related to robotics and autonomous systems, respectively. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with circular target spaces and uses circular statistics, which is related to multimedia applications. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category.
